:: Church Puzzle {"position":"550,1200","size":"100,100"}
The Vicar steps back, and the collection box glows faintly. Text appears on its polished surface, written in two distinct styles: one crisp and clean, the other soft and blurry. "Answer the Three Sacred Verses," it commands.

<div class="church-quiz">

  <!-- Question 1 (Vector) -->
  <div class="question">
    <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;">1. "Hark, I am born of mathematics, not of pigment. My form is a promise, from point to point, a path of pure logic. Enlarge me to the heavens, and I shall not falter, for my lines are eternal and my quality absolute."</p>
    <p><strong>What am I?</strong></p>
    <<radiobutton "_q1" "wrong1" autocheck>> A Pixel<br>
    <<radiobutton "_q1" "correct">> A Vector<br>
    <<radiobutton "_q1" "wrong2">> An Algorithm<br>
  </div>

  <!-- Question 2 (Raster) -->
  <div class="question">
    <p style="font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; filter: blur(0.3px);">2. "Behold, I am a tapestry of a million finite squares, a mosaic of earthly specks. Each colored stone is my lifeblood. Stretch me beyond my means, and my truth becomes a blur, my edges lost to the grid that defines me."</p>
    <p><strong>What am I?</strong></p>
    <<radiobutton "_q2" "wrong1">> A Compression<br>
    <<radiobutton "_q2" "wrong2">> A JPEG<br>
    <<radiobutton "_q2" "correct">> A Raster (or Bitmap)<br>
  </div>

  <!-- Question 3 (Rasterization) -->
  <div class="question">
    <p>3. "When the perfect, scalable line of the Vector is made common, captured and bound to the earthly grid of the Raster, its infinite potential is made finite. This divine sacrifice is known as...?"</p>
    <<radiobutton "_q3" "wrong1" autocheck>> Compression<br>
    <<radiobutton "_q3" "correct">> Rasterization<br>
    <<radiobutton "_q3" "wrong2">> Rendering<br>
  </div>

</div>

<div class="start-menu" style="margin-top: 1.5em;">
  <<link "Offer your knowledge">>
    <<set _score to 0>>
    <<if _q1 is "correct">><<set _score += 1>><</if>>
    <<if _q2 is "correct">><<set _score += 1>><</if>>
    <<if _q3 is "correct">><<set _score += 1>><</if>>

    <<if _score is 3>>
      <<set $clues.ipres_flyer = true>>
      <<replace ".church-quiz">>
        <div class="letter-style" style="text-align:center;">
          <h2 style="color: #22c55e;">THE PATH IS REVEALED</h2>
          <p>The collection box clicks open with a satisfying chime. Inside, there are no coins, only a single, immaculately designed flyer.</p>
          <hr>
          <p><strong>HOST THE iPRES FESTIVAL IN CHECKSUM-ON-THE-WOLD!</strong></p>
          <p><i>A unique opportunity to put our village on the international stage. Sir Regex's traditionalist views threaten our progress. His... removal... would be the ultimate publicity event. The world must see our ambition. All measures are justified for the greater good of preservation.</i></p>
          <hr>
          <p>The flyer is cold and calculating. The Vicar wasn't just planning an event; he saw murder as a marketing opportunity.</p>
          <div class="start-menu">
            <button class="button" data-passage="Explore the Church">Return to the nave</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      <</replace>>
    <<else>>
      <<replace ".church-quiz">>
        <div class="comic-sans-letter" style="text-align:center;">
          <h2 style="color: #ef4444;">YOUR OFFERING IS INVALID</h2>
          <p>A harsh grinding sound comes from the box, and the slot seals shut permanently. A wisp of pixelated smoke drifts out.</p>
          <p>Vicar Vector's face becomes entirely blurry. "A pity," Reverend Raster hisses. "Your understanding is... lossy. The path is now closed to you."</p>
          <p>A cheerful chime echoes from the pews.</p>
          <p>"It looks like you're trying to make a donation that wasn't... *properly formatted*," Clippy says, appearing with a collection plate of his own. "Some truths require a higher resolution. May I suggest a different offering?"</p>
          <div class="start-menu">
            <button class="button" data-passage="Day_2_Map">Return to the map</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      <</replace>>
    <</if>>
  <</link>>
</div>



